ault can spend the money almost as if it were deposited directly into his bank account, so long as he works through other incorporated entities — on \u003Ca href=\"https://news.artnet.com/market/lvmh-caillebotte-musee-dorsay-2252434\">philanthropy\u003C/a>, for instance, or to keep his \u003Ca href=\"https://www.superyachtfan.com/yacht/symphony/\">megayacht\u003C/a> afloat or to \u003Ca href=\"https://www.challenges.fr/classement/classement-des-fortunes-de-france/lvmh-comment-la-famille-arnault-compte-reinvestir-ses-2-9-milliards-de-dividendes_863686\">buy more companies\u003C/a>."},{type:"text",value:"Historically, the rich had to pay hefty taxes on corporate profits, the main source of their income. And the wealth they passed on to their heirs was subject to the estate tax. But both taxes have been gutted in recent decades. In 2018, the United States cut its maximum corporate tax rate to 21 percent from 35 percent. And the estate tax has almost disappeared in America. Relative to the wealth of U.S. households, \u003Ca href=\"https://gabriel-zucman.eu/usdina/\">it generates\u003C/a> only a quarter of the tax revenues it raised in the 1970s."},{type:"graphic",value:{media:{assetType:"graphic",assetSlug:"corp.html",breakpointName:void 0,assetErrors:[],html:"\u003C!-- Generated by ai2html v0.120.0 - 2024-05-02 10:14 -->\n\u003C!-- ai file: corp.ai -->\n\u003Cstyle media=\"screen,print\">\n\t#g-corp-box,\n\t#g-corp-box .g-artboard {\n\t\tmargin: 0 auto;\n\t}\n\t#g-corp-box p {\n\t\tmargin: 0;\n\t}\n\t#g-corp-box .g-aiAbs {\n\t\tposition: absolute;\n\t}\n\t#g-corp-box .g-aiImg {\n\t\tposition: absolute;\n\t\ttop: 0;\n\t\tdisplay: block;\n\t\twidth: 100% !important;\n\t}\n\t#g-corp-box .g-aiSymbol {\n\t\tposition: absolute;\n\t\tbox-sizing: border-box;\n\t}\n\t#g-corp-box .g-aiPointText p {\n\t\twhite-space: nowrap;\n\t}\n\t#g-corp-335 {\n\t\tposition: relative;\n\t\toverflow: hidden;\n\t}\n\t#g-corp-335 p {\n\t\tfont-family: nyt-franklin, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\n